The paper discusses a technique for automatic vulnerability fixing using AI and machine learning, which falls under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE) and computer security (cs.CR). The use of sequence-to-sequence learning also suggests a focus on natural language processing and language generation, which could fall under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the evaluation of the system on real-world vulnerabilities suggests a focus on practical applications, which could fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
